  "text": "Géologie, Paris, France) was used to investigate the nano-texture of each layer [CITATION_1] . This TEM is equipped with a CCD camera (GATAN system ORIUS SC100, image size: 4008-2672 pixels). The High Resolution (HR) mode was used. For each layer, small fragments were smoothly extracted and deposited on a TEM copper grid, itself covered by a lace of amorphous carbon film. HRTEM images were then acquired on the very thin parts of the samples (thickness lower than 10 nm) that lay across the carbon grid holes. micrometer-wide slits in order to minimize the irradiated footprint at the sample position. After careful adjustments of the sample, data were collected from 0 to 1 degree of incident angle with a 0.005° step and corrected from irradiated area [CITATION_2] . For data analysis, a Leptos® software based on Parratt formalism was used for X-ray reflectivity calculation.",
